          <br>
        </div>
        <br>
        <hr>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-12">
            <h3>How I use the table, and what columns I look at.</h3>
            <p>You have to look at everything collectively. The columns I mostly look at are ProjMins, Useage%, OvP, ProjTeamScore, Gameline, SalaryAdjust, RecentPerformance, PtsvsPos, and CriteriaRanking. After that I find the best combo of players and throw them in a line. The key to using this table is Trust the Process and HAVE NO BIAS OPINION!</p>

          </div>
          <div class="col-md-12">

          </div>
        </div>
        <br>
        <hr>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-4">
            <p><u>RankingVsPosition</u></p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-8">
            <p>Description: How many minutes a player is projected to play</p>
            <br>
            <p>What to look for: The higher number the better</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <hr>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-4">
            <p><u>TotalOpportunities</u></p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-8">
            <p>Description: How many minutes a player is projected to play</p>
            <br>
            <p>What to look for: <br> QB: Anything above 35<br> RB: Anything above 15<br> WR: Anything above 6<br> TE: Anything above 5<br> K: Anything above 3
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <hr>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-4">
            <p><u>TeamsOffenseVsPosition</u></p>
          </div>
